{
  "name": "medcore_rcm",
  "version": "3.0",
  "description": "MedCore Healthcare Revenue Cycle Management — a US hospital system's RCM dataset spanning 24 months (Jan 2024 - Dec 2025) with 8 named payers, ~125 providers, and a hidden story: one payer (MidState Mutual) silently changed prior authorization rules in July 2025, causing a denial-rate inflection visible only in payer + denial-code + time stratification.",
  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "Atelier Module 2 (MedCore) hidden-story discovery; HireSQL healthcare assessments; SimLab scenarios",
    "version": "1.1",
    "created": "2026-05-10",
    "updated": "2026-05-17",
    "author": "Eddy Mkwambe / Mpingo Systems",
    "scale_target": "50,000 rows; ~6,200 encounters; 24 months Jan 2024 - Dec 2025",
    "currency": "USD",
    "changelog": [
      "v1.0 (2026-05-10): initial draft",
      "v1.1 (2026-05-17): dropped encounters.created_at (caused temporal-logic failures vs encounter_date); lowered patients/providers cardinality mean 75 to 20 to match generation reality; documented payer-count and low-entropy enum exceptions"
    ],
    "story": {
      "summary": "MidState Mutual changed prior authorization rules in July 2025. Claims submitted under old PA assumptions are now denied with CO-197 (prior auth required). Baseline denial rate ~13% holds for all 8 named payers through Jun 2025; from Jul 2025 onward, MidState's denial rate climbs to ~25% with CO-197 share rising from ~5% to ~35% of its denials.",
      "visibility_tiers": [
        "Surface (basic aggregate): SELECT MONTH(filed_at), AVG(denied) GROUP BY month shows overall denial rate creeping up after Jul 2025.",
        "Investigation (medium): SELECT p.name, AVG(denied) FROM claims c JOIN payers p ON c.payer_id=p.id WHERE filed_at>='2025-07' GROUP BY p.name reveals MidState as the outlier. Note: payer.name is the story-relevant identifier (multiple payer.id rows can share the same name due to engine root-sizing).",
        "Root cause (deep): SELECT p.name, d.carc_code, COUNT(*) FROM denials d JOIN claims c ON d.claim_id=c.id JOIN payers p ON c.payer_id=p.id WHERE d.denial_date>='2025-07' GROUP BY p.name, d.carc_code reveals CO-197 spike concentrated in MidState."
      ],
      "enforcement": "Baseline distributions are written into this pack. The time-trended story signal (MidState denial-rate inflection in Jul 2025 + CO-197 weighting) is enforced post-generation by scripts/enforce-medcore-story.ps1 (Stage 7). The enforcer must filter on payer.name (not payer.id) because the engine generates ~12-15 payer rows per named payer."
    },
    "exceptions": [
      {
        "rule": "Payer count should be exactly 8 (one per named payer)",
        "actual": "~125 payer rows at 50K scale (~15 per name on average)",
        "reason": "Engine has no per-table row-count override; payers as a root table is sized by total-rows budget across the cascade. Story-critical filtering uses payer.name (which IS bounded to the 8 declared enum values) instead of payer.id.",
        "approved_by": "Eddy Mkwambe",
        "date": "2026-05-17",
        "future_fix": "Engine feature request: support fixed lookup tables for story-critical small enumerable entities."
      },
      {
        "rule": "examine assess distribution_diversity should be 100",
        "actual": "88 - providers.active_status (entropy 0.34), payers.active_status (0.28), claims.is_duplicate_flag (0.14) flagged as skewed",
        "reason": "These are legitimate domain ratios: 95% of providers ARE active, 98% of claims are NOT duplicates, 0.3% fraud flag rate. The assess metric penalizes near-constant columns but these reflect industry reality (CMS, HFMA citations).",
        "approved_by": "Eddy Mkwambe",
        "date": "2026-05-17"
      }
    ],
    "open_questions": [
      "Charge amount modeling: pack uses lognormal distribution per encounter type. Payment-to-charge ratio varies by payer (commercial ~190% of Medicare allowed) - enforced via Stage 7 script when payment_amount is computed.",
      "Synthetic CPT and ICD-10 codes: pack uses a small synthetic vocabulary (~25 procedure codes, ~30 diagnosis codes) sufficient for the story. Does NOT claim real CPT/ICD-10 fidelity.",
      "Underpayment rate 8% and duplicate claim rate 2%: illustrative-supported within industry plausible ranges; precise authoritative citations not pinned.",
      "Fraud flag rate 0.3%: illustrative within OIG/CMS plausible range."
    ],
    "citations": [
      {
        "field": "Baseline initial denial rate ~13%",
        "claim": "Kodiak Solutions 2024 reported 11.8% average initial claim denial rate, up from 10.2% prior years. Pack uses 13% as midpoint of credible sources.",
        "source": "Kodiak Solutions 2024 RCA benchmarking via Becker's Payer Issues",
        "url": "https://www.beckerspayer.com/payer/claims-denial-rates-up-prior-auth-denials-down-in-2024-report/"
      },
      {
        "field": "Payer-type denial rate variation",
        "claim": "Premier Inc. 2024 survey: commercial 14.8%, Medicare Advantage 15.7%, Managed Medicaid 15.1%, Medicare FFS 8.4%",
        "source": "Premier Inc. 2024 hospital survey via TechTarget",
        "url": "https://www.techtarget.com/revcyclemanagement/feature/Breaking-down-claim-denial-rates-by-healthcare-payer"
      },
      {
        "field": "Hospital payer mix weights",
        "claim": "U.S. hospital payor mix 2023-2024: commercial ~70%, Medicare ~16%, Medicaid ~14%",
        "source": "Definitive Healthcare HospitalView 2025 (CMS Medicare Cost Report basis)",
        "url": "https://www.definitivehc.com/resources/healthcare-insights/breaking-down-us-hospital-payor-mixes"
      },
      {
        "field": "Days in A/R distribution (mean ~45)",
        "claim": "HFMA benchmark target 30-40 days; Kodiak 2024 reports true A/R days increased 5.2% YoY due to denial volume; pack uses 45-day mean to reflect current industry strain",
        "source": "HFMA KPI Guide; HFMA Hospital Financial and Revenue Cycle Benchmarks Dec 2024",
        "url": "https://www.hfma.org/revenue-cycle/kpis/7-kpis-providers-should-be-tracking/"
      },
      {
        "field": "Top CARC denial codes (CO-16, CO-50, CO-97, CO-22, CO-45, CO-197, etc.)",
        "claim": "X12 CARC official list; Medicare FCSO denial guidance; consensus distribution across multiple industry guides",
        "source": "X12.org official CARC list; CMS / FCSO documentation",
        "url": "https://x12.org/codes/claim-adjustment-reason-codes"
      },
      {
        "field": "Encounter type distribution (outpatient 70%, ED 15%, inpatient 10%, observation 5%)",
        "claim": "Industry consensus for general hospital encounter mix; outpatient-dominant",
        "source": "Industry consensus from multiple RCM benchmarking sources",
        "url": "https://www.hfma.org/finance-and-business-strategy/hospital-financial-and-revenue-cycle-benchmarks-paint-a-complicated-picture-heading-into-the-new-year/"
      },
      {
        "field": "Commercial reimbursement at ~190% of Medicare FFS allowed",
        "claim": "Milliman 2024 commercial reimbursement benchmarking estimates national commercial medical reimbursement at ~190% of Medicare FFS rates",
        "source": "Milliman 2024 Commercial Reimbursement Benchmarking",
        "url": "https://www.milliman.com/en/insight/commercial-reimbursement-benchmarking-medicare-ffs-rates"
      },
      {
        "field": "Synthetic CPT/ICD-10 vocabulary, underpayment/duplicate/fraud rates",
        "claim": "Illustrative values within plausible industry ranges; not claiming real-code distribution fidelity",
        "source": "Illustrative - supported by industry context, not specific cited numbers",
        "url": "https://realitydb.dev/docs"
      }
    ]
  },

